<LEADPARA>  Napalm, which allied aircraft have reportedly begun dropping on Iraqi
fortifications and tank obstacles in Kuwait, is one of the simplest but most
effective weapons against enemy troops sheltered in caves, bunkers and other
enclosed places.;    Invented at Harvard University in cooperation with the
U.S. Army during World War II, napalm is essentially jellied gasoline,
thickened with an aluminum-based soap and other ingredients.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Front  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  NAPALM IS SIMPLE, DEADLY WEAPON  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  WAR IN THE GULF
